    "In the scenario A where the Z ′ flavour violating couplings to right-handed fermions vanish, we have 7 shows that when B(B s → µ + µ -) is predicted within its experimental range, the branching ratio B(B s → τ + τ -) is also constrained.",
    "This feature emerges from the numerical scan, and can be understood from the analytic structure of the amplitudes in scenario A.",
    "Indeed, Eq.",
